    <div class="heading" id="about">
        <h1 id="main_heading"><span style="background: black;">ABOUT</span></h1>
    </div>
   
    <div id="abouthim">
        <div id="about_cont">
            <div id="image">
                <img id="king" src="viratpic.jpg">
        
            </div>
            <div id="description">
                <h2 style="color: #EB5B00; font-size: 30px;">VIRAT KOHLI</h2>
                <p style="color: white;text-align: center;font-size: large;line-height: 30px;">Virat Kohli, born on November 5, 1988, in Delhi, is a renowned Indian cricketer known for his exceptional talent and leadership skills. He began his cricket journey at the West Delhi Cricket Academy and rose to prominence by leading India to victory in the 2008 ICC Under-19 World Cup. Kohli made his international debut in 2008 and quickly established himself as one of the world's top batsmen across all formats, known for his aggressive style and consistency. As captain of the Indian cricket team, he led the team to significant victories, including a historic Test series win in Australia. Off the field, Kohli is recognized for his philanthropy through the Virat Kohli Foundation and his commitment to fitness and excellence. He has received numerous accolades, including the ICC Cricketer of the Year award and India's prestigious Padma Shri award.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <hr style="width: 70%;color: white;margin-bottom: 10px;">
    <div class="heading" id="timeline">
        <h1 id="main_heading"><span style="background: black;">TIMELINE</span></h1>
    </div>
    <div id="timelines">
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/3c/19/76/3c1976f9e0e4ab38901ddfab101f154b.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Early Life and Beginnings</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>1988: Born on November 5 in Delhi, India.</li>
                <li>1998: Joined the West Delhi Cricket Academy at age nine, beginning his formal cricket training.</li>
            </ul>
            
        </div>
    
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://img1.hscicdn.com/image/upload/f_auto,t_ds_w_960,q_50/lsci/db/PICTURES/CMS/87800/87876.jpg">

        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Rising Through the Ranks</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2006: Made his debut for the Delhi Ranji team, playing first-class cricket.</li>
                <li>2008:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Captained the Indian U-19 team to victory in the ICC Under-19 Cricket World Cup in Malaysia.</li>
                    <li>Made his ODI debut for India against Sri Lanka on August 18.</li>
                </ul>

            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://im.rediff.com/cricket/2013/jul/06stat1.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>International Breakthrough
            </h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2009: Scored his maiden ODI century against Sri Lanka in December.</li>
                <li>2010: Cemented his place in the Indian ODI team with consistent performances, including a series of half-centuries and centuries.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://im.rediff.com/cricket/2020/jun/20kohli.jpg">

        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Establishing Dominance
            </h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2011:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Made his Test debut against the West Indies in June.</li>
                    <li>Part of the Indian team that won the ICC Cricket World Cup, contributing crucial innings throughout the tournament.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>2012: Scored his first Test century against Australia in Adelaide.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://im.rediff.com/cricket/2013/oct/17stats1.jpg">

        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Leadership and Captaincy

            </h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2013: Became the vice-captain of the Indian ODI team.
                </li>
                <li>2014: Appointed Test captain after MS Dhoni's retirement from Test cricket; scored twin centuries in his first Test as full-time captain against Australia in Adelaide.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://ss-i.thgim.com/public/cricket/ind-vs-aus-2018-19/article25930867.ece/alternates/FREE_385/SSLIVE-VIRATKOHLI">

        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Record-Breaking Years</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2016:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Scored four double centuries in Test matches within a year.</li>
                    <li>Became the fastest player to score 7,500 runs in ODIs.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>2017:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Took over as India's limited-overs captain after MS Dhoni stepped down.</li>
                    <li>Led India to victories in several bilateral series, both at home and abroad.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>2018: Led India to a historic Test series win in Australia, the first-ever by an Asian team on Australian soil.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://assets.gqindia.com/photos/5cfdde4815464163dd596708/4:3/w_1440,h_1080,c_limit/virat.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Continued Excellence</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2019:</li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Became the fastest player to score 11,000 runs in ODI cricket.</li>
                    <li>Led India to the semifinals of the ICC Cricket World Cup in England.</li>
                </ul>
                <li>2020: Played a key role in India's first-ever Test series win in Australia.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://i2.wp.com/files.prokerala.com/news/photos/imgs/1024/india-s-virat-kohli-celebrates-after-scoring-a-1438635.jpg?strip=all">
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>Recent Achievements</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2021: Stepped down as captain of India's T20I team after the ICC T20 World Cup. India reached the semifinals under his leadership.</li>
                <li>2022: Scored his 71st international century in an Asia Cup match against Afghanistan, ending a nearly three-year drought for a century.Made his return to form in T20Is, ending as the highest run-scorer in the ICC T20 World Cup.</li>
                <li>2023: Achieved the milestone of scoring 25,000 runs in international cricket, continuing to be a vital player for India and also completed his 50th ODI century and he is the only one to achieve that.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="child1">
            <img class="timeline_pics" src="https://static.toiimg.com/photo.cms?photoid=111394553">
        </div>
        <div class="child">
            <h2>2024 and Retirement from T20s</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>2024: Played a pivotal role in India's T20 World Cup victory, scoring 76 runs off 59 balls in the final against South Africa and earning the Man of the Match award.</li>
                <li>Announced his retirement from T20Is after the World Cup triumph, focusing on Test and ODI formats.</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>
