    <div id="awards_section" >
        <div class="awardsfrom">
            <h2>International Awards</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="award_names">
            <h3>1 . ICC Awards:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Sir Garfield Sobers Trophy (ICC Cricketer of the Year): 2017, 2018</li>
                <li>ICC ODI Player of the Year: 2012, 2017, 2018</li>
                <li>ICC Test Player of the Year: 2018</li>
                <li>ICC Spirit of Cricket Award: 2019</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>2 . Wisden Cricketers of the Year:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Named as one of the Wisden Cricketers of the Year in 2019</li>
                <li>Named Wisden Leading Cricketer in the World in 2016, 2017, and 2018</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="awardsfrom">
            <h2>National Awards</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="award_names">
            <h3>1 . Padma shri Award</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Awarded India's fourth-highest civilian award in 2017</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>2 . Arjuna Award:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Received in 2013 for his achievements in cricket
                </li>
            </ul>
            <h3>3 . Rajiv Gandhi Khel Ratna Award:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>India’s highest sporting honor, received in 2018</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="awardsfrom">
            <h2>Other Recognitions</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="award_names">
            <h3>1 . Polly Umrigar Award:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Given by the BCCI for being India's international cricketer of the year: 2011–12, 2014–15, 2015–16, 2016–17, 2017–18</li>
            </ul>
            <h3>2 . Ceat International Cricketer of the Year:</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>2011–12, 2013–14, 2018–19</li>
            </ul>
